name: Café de Flore
description: Iconic Saint‑Germain café with wrap‑around terrace perfect for people‑watching. Dogs welcome on terrace; staff can bring water bowls.

name: Les Deux Magots
description: Historic literary café, dogs seen often on terrace. Great for post‑Luxembourg stroll with pup.

name: Angelina (Rivoli)
description: Belle‑Époque tea room, terrace dog‑friendly, popular for hot chocolate.

name: Bois de Boulogne – Allée des Chiens
description: Large forest park with off‑leash paths and ponds. Famous dog community spot.

name: Bois de Vincennes – Lac Daumesnil Dog Zone
description: Eastern Paris forest with canine areas near lakes. Leash in most parts, off‑leash zones marked.

name: Parc Montsouris (dog areas)
description: Landscaped park with dog‑allowed alleys, fountains nearby.

name: Coulée Verte René‑Dumont
description: Elevated greenway on old railway viaduct; leash required; calm in mornings.

name: Canal Saint‑Martin Riverside
description: Flat canal‑side walk with iron footbridges and cafés; lively in afternoons.

name: Forêt de Fontainebleau
description: Huge forest ~1h from Paris, sandy trails, boulders, pine groves. Dogs love it.

name: Île de Loisirs de Cergy‑Pontoise
description: Expansive leisure area with lakeside loops and picnic lawns. Dogs on leash around lakes.

name: Île de Loisirs de Vaires‑Torcy
description: 350‑hectare recreation base with rowing basin. Dogs leashed near banks, not on beaches.

name: Étangs de Meudon
description: Woodland ponds with shaded banks and soft ground. Leash required.

name: Moustaches – Archives
description: Trendy pet concept store with design accessories and treats.

name: Petsochic – Rue Dauphine
description: Luxury pet boutique with leather goods and grooming spa.

name: Animalis – Bercy Village
address: 47 Rue des Pirogues de Bercy, 75012 Paris
description: Large pet store in Bercy Village complex. Stock food, toys, accessories.

name: CHV Frégis
description: Famous 24/7 veterinary referral hospital near Paris.

name: CHV ADVETIA
description: Large modern hospital with 24/7 emergency and specialties.

name: Clinique Vétérinaire Paris 7
description: Central neighborhood clinic for routine care.

name: Dog‑Station Toilettage
description: Popular grooming salon for all breeds, offers baths, trims, and hand stripping.

name: Toutou Chic
description: High‑end grooming, gentle methods, skin‑friendly products.

name: Au Paradis Canin
description: Experienced groomer offering cuts and ear care.

name: Pension du Pont de Sèvres
address: 18 Av. de la Division Leclerc, 92310 Sèvres
description: Family‑style boarding with garden access, near Paris.

name: The Canine Residency
address: Shuttle from Paris to IDF countryside
description: Cage‑free daycare with structured play and rest; daily shuttle from Paris.

name: Le Domaine Câlin
description: Home‑style boarding without cages, small groups in garden property.

name: Canidélite Paris
description: Positive‑reinforcement training network, group sessions, sports.

name: GentleDog Éducation Canine
description: Force‑free trainer, offers puppy and reactivity programs.

name: Parlez‑Vous Chien?
description: Certified behaviorist for recall and leash manners around Vincennes.
